00:28:50.865 --> 00:28:51.665 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sure.

00:28:51.665 --> 00:28:52.465 align:middle line:90%
>>GILLMORE: OK.

00:28:52.465 --> 00:28:53.648 align:middle line:90%
So I wasn't paralyzed--

00:28:53.648 --> 00:28:54.690 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Still paralysis.

00:28:54.690 --> 00:28:55.490 align:middle line:90%
>>GILLMORE: OK.

00:28:55.490 --> 00:28:57.190 align:middle line:90%
So I wasn't actually paralyzed.

00:28:57.190 --> 00:29:00.450 align:middle line:84%
I was in-- my muscles
were not firing correctly

00:29:00.450 --> 00:29:03.520 align:middle line:84%
and my nerves were all
burning and all of that,

00:29:03.520 --> 00:29:04.660 align:middle line:90%
but I wasn't paralyzed.

00:29:04.660 --> 00:29:09.870 align:middle line:84%
But when we think about
emotions, they impact us.

00:29:09.870 --> 00:29:13.970 align:middle line:84%
And so I had always
been very, very--

00:29:13.970 --> 00:29:15.510 align:middle line:90%
I could push through anything.

00:29:15.510 --> 00:29:16.310 align:middle line:90%
I was--

00:29:16.310 --> 00:29:17.220 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Macho girl.

00:29:17.220 --> 00:29:18.435 align:middle line:90%
>>GILLMORE: Macho, exactly.

00:29:18.435 --> 00:29:20.060 align:middle line:84%
I remember like, the
one time my mother

00:29:20.060 --> 00:29:21.930 align:middle line:90%
cried when I was growing up.

00:29:21.930 --> 00:29:24.420 align:middle line:84%
Like, emotions even in
the corporate world.

00:29:24.420 --> 00:29:27.630 align:middle line:84%
It was like, emotions-- leave
your emotions at the door.

00:29:27.630 --> 00:29:30.300 align:middle line:84%
And so it wasn't something
that I would have ever thought

00:29:30.300 --> 00:29:32.110 align:middle line:90%
my emotions couldn't affect me.

00:29:32.110 --> 00:29:33.120 align:middle line:90%
That would be weak.

00:29:33.120 --> 00:29:35.160 align:middle line:90%
I was macho for that.

00:29:35.160 --> 00:29:37.450 align:middle line:90%
But they're very real.

00:29:37.450 --> 00:29:42.450 align:middle line:84%
And if we think about it for
a moment, a lot of people

00:29:42.450 --> 00:29:43.450 align:middle line:90%
do this very thing.

00:29:43.450 --> 00:29:46.350 align:middle line:84%
If we think about
somebody all the time,

00:29:46.350 --> 00:29:48.660 align:middle line:84%
people will go to
the emergency room

00:29:48.660 --> 00:29:50.730 align:middle line:84%
and they think they're
having a heart attack.

00:29:50.730 --> 00:29:54.130 align:middle line:84%
And it turns out they're
actually having a panic attack.

00:29:54.130 --> 00:29:56.820 align:middle line:84%
And they don't realize
they're even experiencing

00:29:56.820 --> 00:29:58.120 align:middle line:90%
panicking emotions.

00:29:58.120 --> 00:30:01.025 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And panicking emotions
feel like heart attacks.

00:30:01.025 --> 00:30:02.460 align:middle line:90%
>>GILLMORE: Exactly.

00:30:02.460 --> 00:30:07.870 align:middle line:84%
And so point being is that
it's like these emotions

00:30:07.870 --> 00:30:11.710 align:middle line:84%
in our subconscious mind are
affecting our physical bodies

00:30:11.710 --> 00:30:13.340 align:middle line:90%
and we don't even realize it.

00:30:13.340 --> 00:30:17.020 align:middle line:84%
And so I had buried all
of these emotions so much

00:30:17.020 --> 00:30:18.517 align:middle line:90%
