00:34:18.340 --> 00:34:19.225 align:middle line:90%
What are they?

00:34:19.225 --> 00:34:20.770 align:middle line:90%
>>GILLMORE: Absolutely.

00:34:20.770 --> 00:34:23.440 align:middle line:84%
So a simple way to think
about the five factors

00:34:23.440 --> 00:34:27.460 align:middle line:84%
is this, is as I started seeing
that different emotions affect

00:34:27.460 --> 00:34:31.300 align:middle line:84%
the physical body, I started
questioning it objectively,

00:34:31.300 --> 00:34:32.750 align:middle line:90%
but wait a second.

00:34:32.750 --> 00:34:37.000 align:middle line:84%
Somebody can be stressed
and not be sick?

00:34:37.000 --> 00:34:40.239 align:middle line:84%
A person can even
have PTSD and not

00:34:40.239 --> 00:34:42.080 align:middle line:90%
have physical illness at all.

00:34:42.080 --> 00:34:44.090 align:middle line:90%
How is that even possible?

00:34:44.090 --> 00:34:47.300 align:middle line:84%
And so as I started
looking at it objectively,

00:34:47.300 --> 00:34:49.659 align:middle line:84%
what I began to
realize was this,

00:34:49.659 --> 00:34:53.197 align:middle line:84%
was that it takes a certain
combination of emotions.

00:34:53.197 --> 00:34:55.489 align:middle line:84%
And a simple way to think
about it is like, this is it.

00:34:55.489 --> 00:34:58.785 align:middle line:84%
If somebody wants to make
cake and they have flour,

00:34:58.785 --> 00:34:59.660 align:middle line:90%
they can't make cake.

00:34:59.660 --> 00:35:02.810 align:middle line:84%
But if they have flour and they
mix it with other ingredients,

00:35:02.810 --> 00:35:03.860 align:middle line:90%
now they can make cake.

00:35:03.860 --> 00:35:05.540 align:middle line:84%
And if they have a
different recipe,

00:35:05.540 --> 00:35:08.840 align:middle line:84%
they can have a
completely different food.

00:35:08.840 --> 00:35:11.820 align:middle line:84%
And so similarly, that's
how I started looking at it,

00:35:11.820 --> 00:35:13.100 align:middle line:90%
where's those ingredients.

00:35:13.100 --> 00:35:15.950 align:middle line:84%
And that's how I figured
out how it was possible

00:35:15.950 --> 00:35:18.560 align:middle line:84%
for somebody to have
multiple personality disorder

00:35:18.560 --> 00:35:22.440 align:middle line:84%
and have one illness and one
personality, but not in another.

00:35:22.440 --> 00:35:24.990 align:middle line:84%
And a completely different
illness and another personality.

00:35:24.990 --> 00:35:28.010 align:middle line:84%
And so these ingredients, if
you will, these five factors--

00:35:28.010 --> 00:35:29.030 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Which are?

00:35:29.030 --> 00:35:32.070 align:middle line:84%
>>GILLMORE: First and
foremost positive expectation,

00:35:32.070 --> 00:35:35.220 align:middle line:84%
optimism, it helps
speed up healing.

00:35:35.220 --> 00:35:36.020 align:middle line:90%
So that.

00:35:36.020 --> 00:35:39.170 align:middle line:84%
Then I call it the
NPPs and the negative--

00:35:39.170 --> 00:35:41.190 align:middle line:90%
Negative Punishment Patterns.

00:35:41.190 --> 00:35:44.570 align:middle line:84%
And these patterns have to
do with guilt or feeling

00:35:44.570 --> 00:35:49.470 align:middle line:84%
bad or self-criticism,
shame, all of that.

00:35:49.470 --> 00:35:53.270 align:middle line:84%
The third one is what I
call the symptom emotion,

00:35:53.270 --> 00:35:57.160 align:middle line:84%
and that is the emotion
that is directly connected

00:35:57.160 --> 00:35:57.960 align:middle line:90%
to the symptom.

00:35:57.960 --> 00:36:00.090 align:middle line:84%
So for example, if
somebody is embarrassed,

00:36:00.090 --> 00:36:02.760 align:middle line:84%
their face turns red
or panic, anxiety,

00:36:02.760 --> 00:36:04.400 align:middle line:90%
but starting to realize--

00:36:04.400 --> 00:36:06.080 align:middle line:90%
somebody might have a--

00:36:06.080 --> 00:36:09.470 align:middle line:84%
for example, somebody
might have neck pain

00:36:09.470 --> 00:36:12.830 align:middle line:84%
and they might feel that
somebody is a pain in the neck

00:36:12.830 --> 00:36:14.070 align:middle line:90%
and that can happen.

00:36:14.070 --> 00:36:19.260 align:middle line:84%
So it depends on the emotion
that's connected to the symptom.

00:36:19.260 --> 00:36:20.850 align:middle line:90%
So that's number 3.

00:36:20.850 --> 00:36:25.440 align:middle line:84%
Number 4 is what I call
our mind-body-soul needs.

00:36:25.440 --> 00:36:29.330 align:middle line:84%
And our mind-body-soul needs
has to do with the emotions

00:36:29.330 --> 00:36:30.180 align:middle line:90%
that we need.

00:36:30.180 --> 00:36:34.200 align:middle line:84%
So for example, we need
love, we need safety,

00:36:34.200 --> 00:36:36.120 align:middle line:90%
we need acknowledgment.

00:36:36.120 --> 00:36:40.970 align:middle line:84%
And so these can be
linked up to illness.

00:36:40.970 --> 00:36:44.450 align:middle line:84%
And a simple way to think
about it is like this.

00:36:44.450 --> 00:36:47.510 align:middle line:84%
Is that maybe you've
heard before somebody

00:36:47.510 --> 00:36:50.060 align:middle line:90%
who gets love from illness.

00:36:50.060 --> 00:36:53.220 align:middle line:84%
And so what can happen is
love can be linked to illness.

00:36:53.220 --> 00:36:56.070 align:middle line:84%
Or if somebody is in fear,
they can create illness.

00:36:56.070 --> 00:36:58.410 align:middle line:84%
Or another way to think
about it is like this,

00:36:58.410 --> 00:37:02.060 align:middle line:84%
is that sometimes people get
it linked up in their childhood

00:37:02.060 --> 00:37:06.642 align:middle line:84%
where we've heard before,
a child may have an owie.

00:37:06.642 --> 00:37:08.100 align:middle line:84%
Have you ever heard
of this before,

00:37:08.100 --> 00:37:09.215 align:middle line:90%
where a little kid has an owie?

00:37:09.215 --> 00:37:10.015 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, yeah.

00:37:10.015 --> 00:37:12.470 align:middle line:84%
>>GILLMORE: And somebody says,
oh, let me kiss your owie

00:37:12.470 --> 00:37:13.270 align:middle line:90%
and make it better.

00:37:13.270 --> 00:37:14.320 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And it does.

00:37:14.320 --> 00:37:16.830 align:middle line:84%
>>GILLMORE: Well,
actually, at that moment,

00:37:16.830 --> 00:37:18.810 align:middle line:84%
love can get linked
up to illness.

00:37:18.810 --> 00:37:21.530 align:middle line:84%
And at a subconscious
level, somebody

00:37:21.530 --> 00:37:25.410 align:middle line:84%
can link up, that illness
gets love and connection.

00:37:25.410 --> 00:37:28.260 align:middle line:84%
So-- so what I'm saying is
that the mind can be miswired.

00:37:28.260 --> 00:37:31.600 align:middle line:90%
And so that's the fourth factor.

